                    "Most personal finance apps show you pie charts of your spending categories. That's table stakes—and it's not enough to change behaviour. The question users are really asking isn't 'where did my money go?' but 'am I on track, and what should I do next?'",
                    "We design financial dashboards that answer the questions people actually have. Am I spending more than last month? Will I have enough for rent? How close am I to my savings goal? The visualisations are clean and simple, the language is plain and encouraging, and every data point connects to a specific action the user can take. It's the difference between a reporting tool and a financial companion."
